    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Build America Bonds Act of 2015</strong></p> <p> Amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to build America bonds,&nbsp;to: (1) make permanent the issuance authority for such bonds&nbsp;and the authority for payments to bond issuers, (2) make phased reductions in the credit percentage to bondholders and in the&nbsp;percentage of payments to issuers of such bonds, (3) make federal wage rate and other grant requirements applicable to such bonds, (4) allow refundings of currently-issued bonds, and (5) allow the use of such bonds to fund capital expenditures for levees and flood control projects.</p> Provides for an increase in payments to issuers of build America bonds to compensate for reductions in the amount of such payments due to sequestration.]]></text>
